! Set Right Alt as a Mode Switcher
keycode 108 = Mode_switch

! Map Umlaut to <Key> + Mode_switch
keycode 34 = bracketleft  braceleft  udiaeresis Udiaeresis
keycode 35 = bracketright braceright otilde     Otilde
keycode 47 = semicolon    colon      odiaeresis Odiaeresis
keycode 48 = apostrophe   quotedbl   adiaeresis Adiaeresis

! note if our assigned Mode_switch is also mapped by say kanata, then it'll
! mask the events from xmodmap (see https://github.com/jtroo/kanata/discussions/1992)
!
! one solution to work around it per above discussion, we make kanata emit unused
! keycodes (as per `xmodmap -pke`) instead, that are _also_ mapped by xmodmap:
!keycode 248 = odiaeresis Odiaeresis
! another solution is to change kanata logic, which we're currently using.

!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!
! unsure why, but this doesn't toggle player play status:
!keycode 30 = u U XF86AudioPlay

!keycode 43 = h H Left
!keycode 44 = j J Down
!keycode 45 = k K Up
!keycode 46 = l L Right

